presume that he was best suited to acting as a target-man who could hold the ball up and bring others into play. This season, he was encouraged to play facing the goal more. He scored 23 times. Giampiero Ventura, out of work since failing to qualify Italy to the 2018 World Cup, returned to management with Chievo in October. He presided over three defeats and a draw before handing in his resignation. He was, as the journalist Giovanni Capuano observed, ‚Äúonly 363 days late‚Äù. Ronaldo was supposed to be the signing that allowed Juventus to win the Champions League. Instead, they crashed out against Ajax. The football was often drab, and Massimiliano Allegri lost his job. Still, Ronaldo was the best individual performer in a team that won Serie A at a stroll. If Juventus were able to take 24 wins and three draws from their first 27 league games, it was in part because they had a player who could resolve everything on his own even when they were playing badly. More was hoped for. But only because the bar was set high to begin with. Zapata misses penalty to equalise from 3-0 down against Roma. Scores 45 seconds later anyway. After scoring the only goal in a win over Fiorentina, Frosinone‚Äôs Daniel Ciofani lamented leaving himself out of his fantasy team. He was then asked whether his friends had allowed him buy himself cheaply in the preseason auction. ‚ÄúThey let me pay [the minimum price] ‚Ç¨1m,‚Äù confirmed Ciofani. ‚ÄúNot to do me a favour, but because I‚Äôm the centre-forward for Frosinone.‚Äù Honourable mention: Kevin-Prince Boateng, asked on the eve of the season if he could be Sassuolo‚Äôs Ronaldo. ‚ÄúMaybe, yes. But I‚Äôm short by 500 goals.‚Äù Spal‚Äôs supporters went all-out to remind Mattia Destro of the open goal he had missed against them a season before. I tifosi della Spal ricordano il clamoroso errore di Destro l‚Äôanno scorso #SpalBologna pic.twitter.com/nDWDemviXE The Inter fan who turned his back on Mauro Icardi in favour of a true club legend. ‚Äú